{
  "name": "Insect Jamming",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Clans/Aburame.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You spread hungry and festering insects around you in an attempt to secretly infest other creatures of your choice. Select any number of creatures of your choice within range. Creatures must make a constitution saving throw, but remain unaware what you have done unless they have Chakra sight or can sense chakra via Chakra Sensing<br />On a failed save creatures becomes lightly infested with your insects. A creature who is infested can become aware if they take the Search skill action vs your save DC.</p><p>Regardless, for the duration, infested creatures who would cast a jutsu that requires any of the following components, they increase the base cost of the jutsu by +4 for each component the jutsu cast has;</p><p>• Hand Seals (HS)</p><p>• Chakra molding (CM)</p><p>• Chakra Seals (CS)</p><p>• Mobility (M)</p>",
